<div id="ftn390">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref390" name="_ftn390" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">390</sup></span></a> </span>&ldquo;The Wisconsin Idea,&rdquo; University of Wisconsin-Madison,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.wisc.edu/wisconsin-idea/">https://www.wisc.edu/wisconsin-idea/</a>, accessed August 30, 2020.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn391">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref391" name="_ftn391" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">391</sup></span></a> </span>Before Bayh-Dole, many universities relied on external patent management programs. Some universities set up their own research foundations that were separate but affiliated with the actual institution.&nbsp;The Wisconsin Alumni Research Foundation (WARF) is said to be one of the first university intellectual property organizations. In 1948, WARF made a fortune off its discovery of warfarin, a common medication used as a blood thinner for heart disease. WARF&rsquo;s success caught the attention of many universities. Other universities that were involved with licensing prior to 1980 include MIT, the University of California system, and Stanford University. David C. Mowery, Richard R. Nelson, Bhaven N. Sampat &amp; Arvids A. Ziedonis, &ldquo;The Growth of Patenting and Licensing By U.S. Universities: An Assessment of the Effects of the Bayh&ndash;Dole Act of 1980,&rdquo;<i>Research Policy&nbsp;</i>30, no.1 (2001),&nbsp;<a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0048-7333(99)00100-6">https://doi.org/10.1016/S0048-7333(99)00100-6</a>; &ldquo;The Winding Story of Warfarin,&rdquo; University of Wisconsin-Madison, accessed November 25, 2020,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.allwaysforward.org/feature/thank-you-saint-croix-county/">https://www.allwaysforward.org/feature/thank-you-saint-croix-county/</a>; &ldquo;WARF &amp; The Bayh-Dole Act,&rdquo; WARF, accessed November 25, 2020,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.warf.org/about-warf/history/warf-the-bayh-dole-act/">https://www.warf.org/about-warf/history/warf-the-bayh-dole-act/</a>.</p>
</div>
