<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref477" name="_ftn477" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">477</sup></span></a> </span>Preston Mueller, &ldquo;The Non-Dischargeability of Private Student Loans: A Looming Financial Crisis?,&rdquo;&nbsp;<i>Emory Bankruptcy Developments Journal</i>, Emory University, 2015, 237-238,&nbsp;<a href="https://law.emory.edu/ebdj/_documents/volumes/32/1/mueller.pdf">https://law.emory.edu/ebdj/_documents/volumes/32/1/mueller.pdf</a>.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn478">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref478" name="_ftn478" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">478</sup></span></a> </span>&ldquo;Tuition &amp; Fees Historical Trends: AY 1970-AY 2021,&rdquo; Analytics &amp; Institutional Research, University of Kansas, July 2020,&nbsp;<a href="https://air.ku.edu/interactive_factbook/tuition-and-required-fees">https://air.ku.edu/interactive_factbook/tuition-and-required-fees</a>.&nbsp;These and the following calculations all assume that the student in question is earning the federal minimum wage.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn479">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref479" name="_ftn479" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">479</sup></span></a> </span><i>When Congress Went to College: Comparing Tuition Then and Now At Our Elected Officials&rsquo; Alma Maters</i>, Demos,February 15, 2018, 21,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.demos.org/sites/default/files/publications/DEMOS_DFC_Yearbook_FA_Optimized_0.pdf">https://www.demos.org/sites/default/files/publications/DEMOS_DFC_Yearbook_FA_Optimized_0.pdf</a>.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn480">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref480" name="_ftn480" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">480</sup></span></a> </span>&ldquo;Vanderbilt 2020 Tuition &amp; Fees and COA,&rdquo; UnivStats,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.univstats.com/colleges/vanderbilt-university/cost-of-attendance/#:~:text=For%20academic%20year%202019%2D2020,school%20tuition%20%26%20fees%20is%20%2449%2C124">https://www.univstats.com/colleges/vanderbilt-university/cost-of-attendance/#:~:text=For%20academic%20year%202019%2D2020,school%20tuition%20%26%20fees%20is%20%2449%2C124</a>.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn481">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref481" name="_ftn481" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">481</sup></span></a> </span>Jonathan Berr, &ldquo;Why Many Teens No Longer Even Look for a Summer Job,&rdquo;&nbsp;<i>CBS News</i>, May 7, 2018,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.cbsnews.com/news/why-many-teens-no-longer-even-look-for-a-summer-job/">https://www.cbsnews.com/news/why-many-teens-no-longer-even-look-for-a-summer-job/</a>.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn482">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref482" name="_ftn482" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">482</sup></span></a> </span>&ldquo;Common Data Set,&rdquo; Analytics &amp; Institutional Research, University of Kansas, November 1, 2019,&nbsp;<a href="https://air.ku.edu/sites/air.ku.edu/files/files/Common/CDS19_20/H.pdf">https://air.ku.edu/sites/air.ku.edu/files/files/Common/CDS19_20/H.pdf</a>.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn483">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref483" name="_ftn483" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">483</sup></span></a> </span>&ldquo;Vanderbilt Financial Aid,&rdquo; UnivStats,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.univstats.com/colleges/vanderbilt-university/financial-aid/">https://www.univstats.com/colleges/vanderbilt-university/financial-aid/</a>.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn484">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref484" name="_ftn484" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">484</sup></span></a> </span>Jason Delisle,&nbsp;<i>The Surprising Role of High-Income Families in Student Debt Trends: Examining Undergraduate Borrowing by Income, 1995&ndash;96 to 2015&ndash;16</i>, American Enterprise Institute, December 2019,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.aei.org/research-products/report/the-surprising-role-of-high-income-families-in-student-debt-trends-examining-undergraduate-borrowing-by-income-1995-96-to-2015-16/">https://www.aei.org/research-products/report/the-surprising-role-of-high-income-families-in-student-debt-trends-examining-undergraduate-borrowing-by-income-1995-96-to-2015-16/</a>.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn485">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref485" name="_ftn485" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">485</sup></span></a> </span>Another explanation for an increase in borrowing could be that students use it as a form of&nbsp;<i>arbitrage</i>. A student could use student loans, or other capital made available by having student loans, to invest in more profitable enterprises; they could then use the proceeds both to repay their loans and to make a small profit. Yet few students appear to know about this possibility, and even fewer would be in a position to take advantage of it. Ian Shelton, Kathryn Orovecz, &amp; Taciana Faria,&nbsp;<i>Student Loans and the Opportunity for Arbitrage</i>, University of Florida, 2013,&nbsp;<a href="https://ufdc.ufl.edu/AA00061086/00001">https://ufdc.ufl.edu/AA00061086/00001</a>. Arbitrage in this case can be a risky tactic: see &ldquo;Arbitrage, Miscalculation, And A Scarlet Letter &ndash; My Student Loan Story,&rdquo;&nbsp;<i>Planting Our Pennies&nbsp;</i>[blog], accessed January 26, 2021,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.plantingourpennies.com/arbitrage-miscalculation-and-a-scarlet-letter-my-student-loan-story/">https://www.plantingourpennies.com/arbitrage-miscalculation-and-a-scarlet-letter-my-student-loan-story/</a>.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn486">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT" style="background:white"><a href="#_ftnref486" name="_ftn486" title=""><span contenteditable="false" tabindex="-1"><sup data-widget="footnotemarker">486</sup></span></a> </span>Confidential, interview with author via phone, March 2, 2020.</p>
